comment: After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court was upheld and Sacramento retained possession.
Beasley (MIA) makes contact Cousins' (SAC) as he catches the ball.
Cousins (SAC) is fouled by both Beasley (MIA) and Wade (MIA), but Wade contact precedes that of Beasley and call should have been on Wade.
Andersen (MIA) sets the screen on Gay (SAC) and gives him the opportunity to stop and/or change direction.
LHH shows Miller (SAC) creating the contact with Andersen (MIA) as he (Miller) drives to the basket.
Even though Andersen (MIA) does not remain vertical in his attempt to defend Gay (SAC) on his driving layup, RHH shows incidental contact occurs after the ball has been released.
Walker (MIA) contests Cousins' (SAC) putback attempt. Cousins falls to the floor after time expires.
LHH shows Andersen (MIA) remains vertical when contact occurs with McCallum (SAC), turning only after shot is taken in attempt to play the ball.
Andersen (MIA) sets a screen on Gay (SAC), giving him the opportunity to stop and/or change direction.
RHH shows Andersen (MIA) cleanly blocks the layup attempt by Cousins (SAC).
McLemore (SAC) jumps into Andersen (MIA) on his shot attempt, making contact with his body and arms.

After communicating with the Replay Center, the blocking foul was upheld. Referees may initiate replay to see if a defender was in/outside the RA. However, during the review, they may also consider whether the defender was in a legal guarding position.
LHH shows Cousins (SAC) slides into Chalmers (MIA) as he begins his upward shooting motion.
McCallum (SAC) makes contact with Andersen (MIA) and the contact affects his movement to the basket.
Chalmers (MIA) makes body contact to Gay (SAC) on his drive toward the basket. This affects his RSBQ.
McLemore (SAC) commits a take foul on Wade (MIA).
Walker (MIA) jumps vertically as he contests the drive to the basket by McLemore (SAC).
Miller (SAC) commits a take foul on Wade (MIA).
McCallum (SAC) commits a take foul on Wade (MIA).
Andersen (MIA) dislodges Miller (SAC), as he attempts to get the rebound.
